3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* dict_proxy 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* generic dictionary proxy client
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <dict_proxy.h>
10/*
11/* DICT *dict_proxy_open(map, open_flags, dict_flags)
12/* const char *map;
13/* int open_flags;
14/* int dict_flags;
15/* DESCRIPTION
16/* dict_proxy_open() relays read-only or read-write operations
17/* through the Postfix proxymap server.
18/*
19/* The \fIopen_flags\fR argument must specify O_RDONLY
20/* or O_RDWR. Depending on this, the client
21/* connects to the proxymap multiserver or to the
22/* proxywrite single updater.
23/*
24/* The connection to the Postfix proxymap server is automatically
25/* closed after $ipc_idle seconds of idle time, or after $ipc_ttl
26/* seconds of activity.
27/* SECURITY
28/* The proxy map server is not meant to be a trusted process. Proxy
29/* maps must not be used to look up security sensitive information
30/* such as user/group IDs, output files, or external commands.
31/* SEE ALSO
32/* dict(3) generic dictionary manager
33/* clnt_stream(3) client endpoint connection management
34/* DIAGNOSTICS
35/* Fatal errors: out of memory, unimplemented operation,
36/* bad request parameter, map not approved for proxy access.
37/* LICENSE
38/* .ad
39/* .fi
40/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
41/* AUTHOR(S)
42/* Wietse Venema
43/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
44/* P.O. Box 704
45/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
46/*--*/
47

71/* Application-specific. */
72
73typedef struct {
74 DICT dict; /* generic members */
75 CLNT_STREAM *clnt; /* client handle (shared) */
76 const char *service; /* service name */
77 int inst_flags; /* saved dict flags */
78 VSTRING *reskey; /* result key storage */
79 VSTRING *result; /* storage */
80} DICT_PROXY;
81
82 /*
83 * SLMs.
84 */
85#define STR(x) vstring_str(x)
86#define VSTREQ(v,s) (strcmp(STR(v),s) == 0)
87
88 /*
89 * All proxied maps of the same type share the same query/reply socket.
90 */
91static CLNT_STREAM *proxymap_stream; /* read-only maps */
92static CLNT_STREAM *proxywrite_stream; /* read-write maps */
93
94/* dict_proxy_sequence - find first/next entry */
95
96static int dict_proxy_sequence(DICT *dict, int function,
97 const char **key, const char **value)
98{
99 const char *myname = "dict_proxy_sequence";
100 DICT_PROXY *dict_proxy = (DICT_PROXY *) dict;
101 VSTREAM *stream;
102 int status;
103 int count = 0;
104 int request_flags;
105
106 /*
107 * The client and server live in separate processes that may start and
108 * terminate independently. We cannot rely on a persistent connection,
109 * let alone on persistent state (such as a specific open table) that is
110 * associated with a specific connection. Each lookup needs to specify
111 * the table and the flags that were specified to dict_proxy_open().
112 */
113 VSTRING_RESET(dict_proxy->reskey);
114 VSTRING_TERMINATE(dict_proxy->reskey);
115 VSTRING_RESET(dict_proxy->result);
116 VSTRING_TERMINATE(dict_proxy->result);
117 request_flags = dict_proxy->inst_flags
118 | (dict->flags & DICT_FLAG_RQST_MASK);
119 for (;;) {
120 stream = clnt_stream_access(dict_proxy->clnt);
121 errno = 0;
122 count += 1;
123 if (attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
124 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_REQ, PROXY_REQ_SEQUENCE),
125 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_TABLE, dict->name),
126 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, request_flags),
127 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FUNC, function),
128 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 0
129 || vstream_fflush(stream)
130 || attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
131 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
132 RECV_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_KEY, dict_proxy->reskey),
133 RECV_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_VALUE, dict_proxy->result),
134 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 3) {
135 if (msg_verbose || count > 1 || (errno && errno != EPIPE && errno != ENOENT))
136 msg_warn("%s: service %s: %m", myname, VSTREAM_PATH(stream));
137 } else {
138 if (msg_verbose)
139 msg_info("%s: table=%s flags=%s func=%d -> status=%d key=%s val=%s",
140 myname, dict->name, dict_flags_str(request_flags),
141 function, status, STR(dict_proxy->reskey),
142 STR(dict_proxy->result));
143 switch (status) {
144 case PROXY_STAT_BAD:
145 msg_fatal("%s sequence failed for table \"%s\" function %d: "
146 "invalid request",
147 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, function);
148 case PROXY_STAT_DENY:
149 msg_fatal("%s service is not configured for table \"%s\"",
150 dict_proxy->service, dict->name);
151 case PROXY_STAT_OK:
152 *key = STR(dict_proxy->reskey);
153 *value = STR(dict_proxy->result);
154 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, DICT_STAT_SUCCESS);
155 case PROXY_STAT_NOKEY:
156 *key = *value = 0;
157 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, DICT_STAT_FAIL);
158 case PROXY_STAT_RETRY:
159 *key = *value = 0;
160 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_RETRY, DICT_STAT_ERROR);
161 case PROXY_STAT_CONFIG:
162 *key = *value = 0;
163 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_CONFIG, DICT_STAT_ERROR);
164 default:
165 msg_warn("%s sequence failed for table \"%s\" function %d: "
166 "unexpected reply status %d",
167 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, function, status);
168 }
169 }
170 clnt_stream_recover(dict_proxy->clnt);
171 sleep(1); /* XXX make configurable */
172 }
173}

175/* dict_proxy_lookup - find table entry */
176
177static const char *dict_proxy_lookup(DICT *dict, const char *key)
178{
179 const char *myname = "dict_proxy_lookup";
180 DICT_PROXY *dict_proxy = (DICT_PROXY *) dict;
181 VSTREAM *stream;
182 int status;
183 int count = 0;
184 int request_flags;
185
186 /*
187 * The client and server live in separate processes that may start and
188 * terminate independently. We cannot rely on a persistent connection,
189 * let alone on persistent state (such as a specific open table) that is
190 * associated with a specific connection. Each lookup needs to specify
191 * the table and the flags that were specified to dict_proxy_open().
192 */
193 VSTRING_RESET(dict_proxy->result);
194 VSTRING_TERMINATE(dict_proxy->result);
195 request_flags = dict_proxy->inst_flags
196 | (dict->flags & DICT_FLAG_RQST_MASK);
197 for (;;) {
198 stream = clnt_stream_access(dict_proxy->clnt);
199 errno = 0;
200 count += 1;
201 if (attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
202 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_REQ, PROXY_REQ_LOOKUP),
203 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_TABLE, dict->name),
204 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, request_flags),
205 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_KEY, key),
206 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 0
207 || vstream_fflush(stream)
208 || attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
209 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
210 RECV_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_VALUE, dict_proxy->result),
211 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 2) {
212 if (msg_verbose || count > 1 || (errno && errno != EPIPE && errno != ENOENT))
213 msg_warn("%s: service %s: %m", myname, VSTREAM_PATH(stream));
214 } else {
215 if (msg_verbose)
216 msg_info("%s: table=%s flags=%s key=%s -> status=%d result=%s",
217 myname, dict->name,
218 dict_flags_str(request_flags), key,
219 status, STR(dict_proxy->result));
220 switch (status) {
221 case PROXY_STAT_BAD:
222 msg_fatal("%s lookup failed for table \"%s\" key \"%s\": "
223 "invalid request",
224 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, key);
225 case PROXY_STAT_DENY:
226 msg_fatal("%s service is not configured for table \"%s\"",
227 dict_proxy->service, dict->name);
228 case PROXY_STAT_OK:
229 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, STR(dict_proxy->result));
230 case PROXY_STAT_NOKEY:
231 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, (char *) 0);
232 case PROXY_STAT_RETRY:
233 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_RETRY, (char *) 0);
234 case PROXY_STAT_CONFIG:
235 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_CONFIG, (char *) 0);
236 default:
237 msg_warn("%s lookup failed for table \"%s\" key \"%s\": "
238 "unexpected reply status %d",
239 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, key, status);
240 }
241 }
242 clnt_stream_recover(dict_proxy->clnt);
243 sleep(1); /* XXX make configurable */
244 }
245}

247/* dict_proxy_update - update table entry */
248
249static int dict_proxy_update(DICT *dict, const char *key, const char *value)
250{
251 const char *myname = "dict_proxy_update";
252 DICT_PROXY *dict_proxy = (DICT_PROXY *) dict;
253 VSTREAM *stream;
254 int status;
255 int count = 0;
256 int request_flags;
257
258 /*
259 * The client and server live in separate processes that may start and
260 * terminate independently. We cannot rely on a persistent connection,
261 * let alone on persistent state (such as a specific open table) that is
262 * associated with a specific connection. Each lookup needs to specify
263 * the table and the flags that were specified to dict_proxy_open().
264 */
265 request_flags = dict_proxy->inst_flags
266 | (dict->flags & DICT_FLAG_RQST_MASK);
267 for (;;) {
268 stream = clnt_stream_access(dict_proxy->clnt);
269 errno = 0;
270 count += 1;
271 if (attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
272 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_REQ, PROXY_REQ_UPDATE),
273 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_TABLE, dict->name),
274 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, request_flags),
275 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_KEY, key),
276 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_VALUE, value),
277 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 0
278 || vstream_fflush(stream)
279 || attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
280 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
281 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1) {
282 if (msg_verbose || count > 1 || (errno && errno != EPIPE && errno != ENOENT))
283 msg_warn("%s: service %s: %m", myname, VSTREAM_PATH(stream));
284 } else {
285 if (msg_verbose)
286 msg_info("%s: table=%s flags=%s key=%s value=%s -> status=%d",
287 myname, dict->name, dict_flags_str(request_flags),
288 key, value, status);
289 switch (status) {
290 case PROXY_STAT_BAD:
291 msg_fatal("%s update failed for table \"%s\" key \"%s\": "
292 "invalid request",
293 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, key);
294 case PROXY_STAT_DENY:
295 msg_fatal("%s update access is not configured for table \"%s\"",
296 dict_proxy->service, dict->name);
297 case PROXY_STAT_OK:
298 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, DICT_STAT_SUCCESS);
299 case PROXY_STAT_NOKEY:
300 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_NONE, DICT_STAT_FAIL);
301 case PROXY_STAT_RETRY:
302 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_RETRY, DICT_STAT_ERROR);
303 case PROXY_STAT_CONFIG:
304 DICT_ERR_VAL_RETURN(dict, DICT_ERR_CONFIG, DICT_STAT_ERROR);
305 default:
306 msg_warn("%s update failed for table \"%s\" key \"%s\": "
307 "unexpected reply status %d",
308 dict_proxy->service, dict->name, key, status);
309 }
310 }
311 clnt_stream_recover(dict_proxy->clnt);
312 sleep(1); /* XXX make configurable */
313 }

385/* dict_proxy_close - disconnect */
386
387static void dict_proxy_close(DICT *dict)
388{
389 DICT_PROXY *dict_proxy = (DICT_PROXY *) dict;
390
391 vstring_free(dict_proxy->reskey);
392 vstring_free(dict_proxy->result);
393 dict_free(dict);
394}
395
396/* dict_proxy_open - open remote map */
397
398DICT *dict_proxy_open(const char *map, int open_flags, int dict_flags)
399{
400 const char *myname = "dict_proxy_open";
401 DICT_PROXY *dict_proxy;
402 VSTREAM *stream;
403 int server_flags;
404 int status;
405 const char *service;
406 char *relative_path;
407 char *kludge = 0;
408 char *prefix;
409 CLNT_STREAM **pstream;
410
411 /*
412 * If this map can't be proxied then we silently do a direct open. This
413 * allows sites to benefit from proxying the virtual mailbox maps without
414 * unnecessary pain.
415 */
416 if (dict_flags & DICT_FLAG_NO_PROXY)
417 return (dict_open(map, open_flags, dict_flags));
418
419 /*
420 * Use a shared stream for proxied table lookups of the same type.
421 *
422 * XXX A complete implementation would also allow O_RDWR without O_CREAT.
423 * But we must not pass on every possible set of flags to the proxy
424 * server; only sets that make sense. For now, the flags are passed
425 * implicitly by choosing between the proxymap or proxywrite service.
426 *
427 * XXX Use absolute pathname to make this work from non-daemon processes.
428 */
429 if (open_flags == O_RDONLY) {
430 pstream = &proxymap_stream;
431 service = var_proxymap_service;
432 } else if ((open_flags & O_RDWR) == O_RDWR) {
433 pstream = &proxywrite_stream;
434 service = var_proxywrite_service;
435 } else
436 msg_fatal("%s: %s map open requires O_RDONLY or O_RDWR mode",
437 map, DICT_TYPE_PROXY);
438
439 if (*pstream == 0) {
440 relative_path = concatenate(MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE "/",
441 service, (char *) 0);
442 if (access(relative_path, F_OK) == 0)
443 prefix = MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE;
444 else
445 prefix = kludge = concatenate(var_queue_dir, "/",
446 MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE, (char *) 0);
447 *pstream = clnt_stream_create(prefix, service, var_ipc_idle_limit,
448 var_ipc_ttl_limit);
449 if (kludge)
450 myfree(kludge);
451 myfree(relative_path);
452 }
453
454 /*
455 * Local initialization.
456 */
457 dict_proxy = (DICT_PROXY *)
458 dict_alloc(DICT_TYPE_PROXY, map, sizeof(*dict_proxy));
459 dict_proxy->dict.lookup = dict_proxy_lookup;
460 dict_proxy->dict.update = dict_proxy_update;
461 dict_proxy->dict.delete = dict_proxy_delete;
462 dict_proxy->dict.sequence = dict_proxy_sequence;
463 dict_proxy->dict.close = dict_proxy_close;
464 dict_proxy->inst_flags = (dict_flags & DICT_FLAG_INST_MASK);
465 dict_proxy->reskey = vstring_alloc(10);
466 dict_proxy->result = vstring_alloc(10);
467 dict_proxy->clnt = *pstream;
468 dict_proxy->service = service;
469
470 /*
471 * Establish initial contact and get the map type specific flags.
472 *
473 * XXX Should retrieve flags from local instance.
474 */
475 for (;;) {
476 stream = clnt_stream_access(dict_proxy->clnt);
477 errno = 0;
478 if (attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
479 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_REQ, PROXY_REQ_OPEN),
480 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_TABLE, dict_proxy->dict.name),
481 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, dict_proxy->inst_flags),
482 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 0
483 || vstream_fflush(stream)
484 || attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
485 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
486 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, &server_flags),
487 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 2) {
488 if (msg_verbose || (errno != EPIPE && errno != ENOENT))
489 msg_warn("%s: service %s: %m", VSTREAM_PATH(stream), myname);
490 } else {
491 if (msg_verbose)
492 msg_info("%s: connect to map=%s status=%d server_flags=%s",
493 myname, dict_proxy->dict.name, status,
494 dict_flags_str(server_flags));
495 switch (status) {
496 case PROXY_STAT_BAD:
497 msg_fatal("%s open failed for table \"%s\": invalid request",
498 dict_proxy->service, dict_proxy->dict.name);
499 case PROXY_STAT_DENY:
500 msg_fatal("%s service is not configured for table \"%s\"",
501 dict_proxy->service, dict_proxy->dict.name);
502 case PROXY_STAT_OK:
503 dict_proxy->dict.flags = (dict_flags & ~DICT_FLAG_IMPL_MASK)
504 | (server_flags & DICT_FLAG_IMPL_MASK);
505 return (DICT_DEBUG (&dict_proxy->dict));
506 default:
507 msg_warn("%s open failed for table \"%s\": unexpected status %d",
508 dict_proxy->service, dict_proxy->dict.name, status);
509 }
510 }
511 clnt_stream_recover(dict_proxy->clnt);
512 sleep(1); /* XXX make configurable */
513 }
